 An alternative route for access to the North and the South between Skukuza rest camp and Tshokwane will be through the low-water bridge just east of Lower Sabie camp Mabasa said.Mabasa said the severe floods had caused serious road damage and the bridge between Skukuza and Tshokwane had been swept away.Mabasa advised visitors who planned to travel between Satara and Skukuza to check the water situation at the Lower Sabie low-water bridge with the reception offices before embarking on their journey.Mabasa reassured visitors that the water would subside and that it would be business as usual in the area even though extra caution was necessary for now. We will keep informing everyone with any new developments. 